### Phase 2.5 — AI Capabilities (The USP)

**2.5a. Verify full Corsair MCP tool surface**
- Read `server/agent/run-agent.ts` and confirm the agent receives ALL Corsair tools for Gmail + Calendar (not a filtered subset)
- If any tools are excluded or scoped down, remove the restrictions — the agent should have the same API surface as the full Corsair integration
- Verify the system prompt instructs the agent to use Corsair tools for all email and calendar tasks, not just "simple" ones

**2.5b. Set cheap model as default**
- Default agent model: `google/gemini-2.0-flash` (already set per memory) or `openai/gpt-4o-mini` via OpenRouter — confirm in `server/agent/run-agent.ts` or `lib/agent-models.ts`
- AI draft button (below) also uses the cheap model
- Expensive model (`gpt-4o`, `claude-opus`) only via user's own API key in settings

**2.5c. Inline AI draft button in compose/reply**

This is the highest-leverage AI feature for daily use. When composing or replying, a single button asks the AI to draft the message based on thread context.

- `components/mail/mail-workspace.tsx` (compose dialog): Add a "Draft with AI" button next to the compose body textarea
- On click: POST to a new `app/api/mail/draft-ai/route.ts` endpoint
- Endpoint sends the thread context (subject, last 3 messages, user's tone from settings) to the LLM, returns a draft string
- Draft populates the compose body — user edits and sends
- Use cheap model (`gpt-4o-mini`) — this is a fast, high-frequency operation
- System prompt for drafting: "You are drafting an email reply for the user. Match their tone. Be concise. Do not add pleasantries they didn't ask for."

**2.5d. Post-action real-time UI update (AI writes → instant inbox refresh)**

When the AI agent executes a write (send email, create event, delete, etc.) — either immediately or after the user approves at `/approvals` — the inbox and calendar must update without a page refresh. This is the loop that makes the AI feel instant.

- The approval execution route (`app/api/approvals/[id]/route.ts`) already calls `syncCorsairPlugin()` after approve — verify this triggers the Inngest sync (after Phase 1 is done)
- With the SSE stream from Phase 2 active, the UI will automatically invalidate React Query and refetch within 2 seconds of the sync completing
- **This means Phase 1 (Inngest) + Phase 2 (SSE) are prerequisites for the AI to feel instant**
- No additional code needed here — just verify the chain works end-to-end: approve → sync → SSE event → React Query invalidate → UI updates

**2.5e. AI action visibility in chat**

The agent chat (float + `/agent` page) should clearly show what Corsair tools were called and what happened — not just a text response. This already exists (tool-call visualization is in `ai-chat-float.tsx`) but verify:
- Tool call names are human-readable (not raw Corsair endpoint strings)
- After a write is executed, the agent confirms with a summary ("Email sent to X. Calendar invite created for Thursday 9am.")
- If approval is needed, the agent message links directly to `/approvals` so the user can approve in one click

