## Evaluation Criteria

A great result means **all of the following pass**:

| # | Test | Pass condition |
|---|------|---------------|
| **AI** | | |
| 1 | AI compound action | "Send a calendar invite to X at 9am Thursday and email them saying I look forward to it" → agent creates event + sends email → both appear in inbox and calendar instantly |
| 2 | AI draft | Click "Draft with AI" in compose/reply → body is populated with a contextually correct draft in the user's tone |
| 3 | AI post-action refresh | After approving an AI write action → inbox/calendar updates without page refresh within 5 seconds |
| 4 | Full tool surface | Ask agent to do any supported Corsair operation (search, label, RSVP, delete, etc.) → it executes correctly |
| **Infrastructure** | | |
| 5 | Real-time email | Trigger a Corsair webhook manually → thread appears in inbox without page refresh |
| 6 | Real-time calendar | Same as above for calendar event |
| 7 | Approval default | New `UserSettings` row has `approvalStrict = "writes"` (verify in Prisma Studio) |
| **Gmail** | | |
| 8 | Reply-All | Reply-all compose populates To field with all recipients, not just original sender |
| 9 | Snooze | Snooze button moves thread out of inbox; thread visible in Snoozed mailbox |
| 10 | Keyboard | Navigate inbox, open thread, reply, archive, compose — mouse never touched (test live) |
| 11 | Labels | Dropdown shows user labels; toggling one applies/removes it and thread label list updates |
| 12 | Search | `from:alice@example.com` in search box returns server-side Gmail results (not just client-filtered) |
| 13 | Attachments | Attachment chip renders on messages with inline data; clicking downloads the file; large attachments show "open in Gmail" message |
| **Calendar** | | |
| 14 | RSVP | Accept/Decline/Maybe buttons appear on events you didn't organize; status updates after clicking |
| 15 | Conflict warning | Creating event overlapping an existing event shows a yellow warning in the dialog |
| 16 | Drag reschedule | Can drag an event to a new time slot in week/day view; event time updates after drop |

**North-star goal (not a pass/fail test):** Use the app as the sole Gmail + Google Calendar interface for one full working day.

